comment:
* A class that contains information about a GNSS antenna. GNSS antenna characteristics can change * with device configuration, such as when a device is folded open or closed. Antenna information is * delivered to registered instances of {@link Listener}. * *

Antenna info parameters are measured for each specific device model by the device * manufacturers and provided to the Android framework.

methods.name: public PhaseCenterOffset getPhaseCenterOffset()
methods.comment:
* Returns a {@link PhaseCenterOffset} object encapsulating the phase center offset and
     * corresponding uncertainties in millimeters.
     *
     * @return {@link PhaseCenterOffset}

methods.name: public SphericalCorrections getPhaseCenterVariationCorrections()
methods.comment:
* Returns a {@link SphericalCorrections} object encapsulating the phase center variation
     * corrections and corresponding uncertainties in millimeters.
     *
     * @return phase center variation corrections as {@link SphericalCorrections}

methods.name: public SphericalCorrections getSignalGainCorrections()
methods.comment:
* Returns a {@link SphericalCorrections} object encapsulating the signal gain
     * corrections and corresponding uncertainties in dBi.
     *
     * @return signal gain corrections as {@link SphericalCorrections}
